        "created_at": "2025-04-06T08:42:37.656Z",
        "cooked": "<p>After a few minutes, the app just going black (or white depending on which light/dark mode is activated). I’m assuming this is some kind of privacy feature if Signal isn’t used for a while, but it’s a little bit annoying as I have it open on a second screen and do want to see new messages come in.</p>\n<p>The contents are shown when the app window is resized again. Clicking into the app doesn’t work.</p>\n<p>Is there a way to deactivate this feature? It doesn’t make sense anyway, since there’s no password request to unlock the app</p>\n<details>\n<summary>\nExample</summary>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/e/8/e8c2803f4881da85dac48d3d677c423f95652a4a.png\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/e8c2803f4881da85dac48d3d677c423f95652a4a\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/e/8/e8c2803f4881da85dac48d3d677c423f95652a4a_2_690x387.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"xd5ulNmCXvWkOQR9MiksTiYtyie\" width=\"690\" height=\"387\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/e/8/e8c2803f4881da85dac48d3d677c423f95652a4a_2_690x387.png, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/e/8/e8c2803f4881da85dac48d3d677c423f95652a4a_2_1035x580.png 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/e/8/e8c2803f4881da85dac48d3d677c423f95652a4a_2_1380x774.png 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"121213\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1915×1075 10.8 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n</details>\n<p><a href=\"https://debuglogs.org/desktop/7.47.0/c9c7558f7320140edaeea